The global rotary steerable system market is expected to witness significant growth during the forecast period of 2021 to 2031. There are several key segments that are driving this growth. In terms of type, the market is segmented into push-the-bit rotary steerable system and point-the-bit rotary steerable system. The push-the-bit system allows for greater control and accuracy in directional drilling, while the point-the-bit system offers advantages in certain drilling conditions. In addition, the market is segmented by application into offshore drilling and onshore drilling. Offshore drilling activities are increasing globally, driving the demand for advanced drilling technologies like rotary steerable systems. Furthermore, the market is segmented by well type, with horizontal wells and vertical wells being key categories. Horizontal wells are becoming increasingly popular due to their higher production rates and increased hydrocarbon recovery.

